# Finance Dashboard UI

A clean and interactive Finance Dashboard built using React.js that allows users to track financial activity, analyse spending patterns, and manage transactions through a responsive dashboard interface.

---

## Live Demo
https://financeedashboard.netlify.app/

## GitHub Repository
https://github.com/perfectcse/Finance-Dashboard-UI

---

## Overview
This project is a frontend finance dashboard interface designed to display financial summaries, transaction data, and spending insights. The dashboard includes charts, summary cards, filters, and role-based UI behavior. The project focuses on UI design, component structure, and state management using React Context API.

---

## Features

### Dashboard Overview
- Total Balance summary card
- Total Income summary card
- Total Expense summary card
- Balance Trend Line Chart
- Spending Breakdown Pie Chart

### Transactions Management
- Transactions table with details
- Search transactions by category
- Filter transactions by type (Income / Expense)
- Role-based UI (Admin / Viewer)
- Admin can add transactions
- viewer can only view data

### Insights Section
- Highest spending category
- Financial activity insights

### State Management
- React Context API
- Global state for transactions, filters, and roles

### UI / UX
- Clean dashboard layout
- Responsive design
- Single global CSS styling
- Card-based dashboard UI

---

## Tech Stack
| Technology | Purpose |
|------------|---------|
| React.js | Frontend framework |
| Context API | State management |
| Recharts | Data visualization |
| CSS | Styling |
| Vite | Development environment |

---
---

## Role-Based Access
| Role | Permissions |
|------|------------|
| Viewer | Can view dashboard and transactions |
| Admin | Can view dashboard and add transactions |

---

## Charts Used
- Line Chart → Balance Trend
- Pie Chart → Spending Breakdown

